Can you explain why the `zcbenchmark` command requires a password to run?

The `zcbenchmark` command does not require a password to run. The command syntax is simply `zcbenchmark benchmarktype samplecount`, and it runs a benchmark of the selected type `samplecount` times, returning the running times of each sample.
What is the default value of `samplecount` if I don't specify it when running the `zcbenchmark` command?
There is no default value for `samplecount`. It is required to specify the `samplecount` when running the `zcbenchmark` command. The correct syntax is `zcbenchmark benchmarktype samplecount`.
